<br>
And as much as people complain about parchments we don't have the problem of only certain spells being availible on very select mobs that are either over camped or hard for most to kill.<br>
<br>
All in all its an awesome expansion for mages.  When I speak some of my displeasure with host of the elements, it's because its been watered down a bit too much for a 12 AA point (for complete version) skill.<br>
<br>
It's cute and it helps push things, but beyond that I really can't give it too much in regards for damage.   I should explain that I'm not mad the ability sucks.  Because it doesn't suck.  But it had all the potential in the world to be a beautiful solid core ability of mages and it was watered down.<br>
<br>
The pets can't tank at all and although thats fair given the rest of the scope of the ability it's one of those things that looks really bad when you compare it to the shamans.<br>
<br>
The micropets are a little too small, but thats personal taste.  Would have liked them all at least dwarf sized.  I'm figuring this was done as to not block line of sight.   I can't see that as a major problem though as most mobs you'd use this against are higher than dwarves and certainly a lot bigger.<br>
<br>
The duration and total damage seems like the worst bit.  Overall higher recast time and higher duration for when it's used I would perfer again.  Using this every 45 mins for 60 seconds worth of pummeling sounds more reasonable than 30 seconds worth every 22 seconds.<br>
<br>
Maybe thats just me too..<br>
<br>
On the lighter side.. Thank god for Firebolt of Tallon..  Its nice to see people actually wanting to choose between using a bolt or a DD spell now.   And it's damn nice to be able to do enough damage with the spell to see the mobs health move than a couple percent.   In other words, its nice to have a NUKE that feels like a NUKE. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wezloc@themagicianstower>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1302<br> <font color=#333333>(11/25/02 10:02:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7896.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Host of the Elements -Description on Test</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>All in all its an awesome expansion for mages. When I speak some of my displeasure with host of the elements, it's because its been watered down a bit too much for a 12 AA point (for complete version) skill.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
